methods.lookup:
Determine the appropriate ObjectCodecType for the supplied "ObjectCodecClass" value.

:param valueToLookup: (java.lang.String) - The name to lookup
:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition.ObjectCodecType) The matching constant, or null if none was found
methods.valueOf:
Returns the enum constant of this type with the specified name.
The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an
enum constant in this type.  (Extraneous whitespace characters are 
not permitted.)

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition.ObjectCodecType) the enum constant with the specified name

text: Object codec types, allowing us to specify whether a "built-in" behavior should be used, or a codec class.
